    "Emotions are a ubiquitous experience, yet also vary from person to person.",
    "If a colleague publishes prolifically, some people might ENVY them, others ADMIRE their output, and a third might feel SAD-NESS about their inability to compete.",
    "But do these emotional patterns follow broader gender lines?",
    "* Equal contribution.",
